class Solution:
    def mirrorDistance(self, n: int) -> int:
        rev = int(str(n)[::-1])
        return abs(n - rev)

"""
Approach & Reasoning:
Convert n to string, reverse the digits, and convert back to integer (which automatically discards leading zeros). Compute the absolute difference between original n and its reversed version.

This directly implements the definition given in the problem. It handles all edge cases correctly:
- Single digit numbers return 0.
- Numbers ending with zeros have their reverse correctly drop leading zeros after reversal.
- Maximum n=10^9 is handled efficiently.

Time Complexity: O(d) where d is the number of digits (≤10)
Space Complexity: O(d) for the string
"""
